{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] --> | name = Christophe Moehrlen | image = Christophe Moehrlen.jpg | caption = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1800|1|20|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Baiersbronn]], [[Württemberg]] | death_date = {{death date and age|1871|2|28|1800|1|20|df=y}} | death_place = [[Daillens]], Switzerland | occupation = Schoolteacher, writer | movement = | genre = [[Children's literature]], Christian literature | notableworks = }} '''Christophe Moehrlen''' (20 January 1800 – 28 February 1871), pen name: '''Christoph Irenius''', was a Swiss French Protestant pastor of German origin, schoolteacher and author of children's literature.
== Biography == [[File:Röschen Friedenauer.jpg|thumb|Christophe Moehrlen's wife: Röschen Friedenauer]] Moehrlen was teacher at the [[Evangelical College in Schiers]],<ref>[[Heinrich Wilhelm Josias Thiersch]]. ''[[Christian Heinrich Zeller]]'s Leben.'' Vol. 1. Felix Schneider, 1876, [https://books.google.com/books?id=KglBAAAAIAAJ&q=%22Christoph+M%C3%B6hrlen%22&dq=%22Christoph+M%C3%B6hrlen%22&hl=pt-BR&ei=q06_TuHnOYG_gQekpNySBw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=9&ved=0CFAQ6AEwCDgU p. 308]</ref> at the poorhouse ''Calame'' in [[Le Locle]]<ref>''Basler Zeitschrift für Geschichte und Altertumskunde'', Vol. 43-45. Historische und Antiquarische Gesellschaft zu Basel, Stiftung Pro Augusta Raurica, R. Reich, 1944. [https://books.google.com/books?id=sdsWAQAAIAAJ&q=%22Christoph+M%C3%B6hrlen%22&dq=%22Christoph+M%C3%B6hrlen%22&hl=pt-BR&ei=q06_TuHnOYG_gQekpNySBw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=6&ved=0CEMQ6AEwBTgU p. 132]</ref> and at [[Christian Friedrich Spittler]]′s ''Griechenanstalt'' in [[Beuggen]].<ref>[[Heidy Margrit Müller]]. ''Dichterische Freiheit und pädagogische Utopie: Studien zur schweizerischen Jugendliteratur.'' Lang, 1998. [https://books.google.com/books?id=b-AHAQAAMAAJ&q=%22Christoph+M%C3%B6hrlen%22&dq=%22Christoph+M%C3%B6hrlen%22&hl=pt-BR&ei=DEO_TuuwH8LogQf4hYGQBw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3&ved=0CDcQ6AEwAg p. 33]. {{ISBN|978-3-906757-56-8}}</ref> He later worked as a pastor in [[Payerne]] where he founded a reformatory for boys, and finally in [[Daillens]].<ref>''Anzeige einer Knaben-Erziehungsanstalt'' in the second volume of his work ''Das Buch der Wahrheitszeugen''. Basel 1846, [https://books.google.com/books?id=NL88AAAAcAAJ&pg=PA829 p. 829]</ref> In addition to some educational works and translations, he published in 1839 under the pseudonym Christoph Irenius the autobiographical book ''Eine wahrhafte Geschichte'' ("A true story").
Moehrlen was the father-in-law of [[Otto Sutermeister]].<ref>[http://www.gen-gen.ch/MOEHRLEN/Christophe/1403459?lg=en Christophe Moehrlen], [[Société Genevoise de Généalogie]]</ref><ref>''Erinnerung an Frau Professor Ernestine Sutermeister-Moehrlen: Geboren den 18. Oktober 1832 / Gestorben den 18. Juli 1900.'' 1900.</ref>
==Selected works== * [https://books.google.com/books?id=ORZGAAAAcAAJ ''Christoph Irenius: Eine wahrhafte Geschichte.''] Autobiography. Basel, 1839. * [https://books.google.com/books?id=38IAAAAAcAAJ ''Geschichte der Waldenser: von ihrem Ursprunge an bis auf unsere Zeit.''] Basel: Bahnmaier's Buchhandlung, C. Detloff, 1844. 99 pages. * ''Das Buch der Wahrheitszeugen oder der theuern protestantisch-evangelischen Kirche ununterbrochene Fortdauer in allen Jahrhunderten. Geschichtserzählungen für Schule und Haus.'' 2 Volumes, Basel 1844-1845 ([http://reader.digitale-sammlungen.de/resolve/display/bsb10484045.html Volume 1] and [http://reader.digitale-sammlungen.de/resolve/display/bsb10484046.html Volume 2] at [[Munich Digitization Center]]) * [https://books.google.com/books?id=Rng7AAAAcAAJ ''Histoire biblique pour les écoles et les familles.''] Translation from German to French. Payerne: [[Louis Gueissaz]], 1850-60.
==Secondary literature== * Marie Dedie-Moehrlen. ''Une belle vie: la vie de mon grand-père, le pasteur Christophe Moehrlen, 1800-1871.'' Neuchâtel: Impr. P. Attinger S.A., 1936. 199 pages. * Olivier Dedie (editor). ''Le dernier journal du pasteur Christophe Moehrlen.'' (from 1866 to 1869) Rolle: Société d'histoire de la Côte, 1987. 32 pages.
