{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}} {{Refimprove|date=December 2009}} {{Infobox newspaper |name = Ha'ir |type = [[Weekly newspaper]] |foundation = October 1980 |format = [[Tabloid (newspaper format)|Tabloid]] |publishing_country = Israel |language = [[Hebrew language|Hebrew]] |editor = Omer Shobert |owners = [[Schocken Books|Schocken]] Group }} '''''Ha'ir''''' ({{Lang-he|העיר}}, lit ''The City'') is a weekly local newspaper published in [[Tel Aviv]], [[Israel]]. The [[Tabloid (newspaper format)|tabloid]]-sized newspaper was first published in October 1980. Since April 2005 when there was a major shakeup in the business structure of newspaper's publisher, [[Schocken Books|Schocken]] Group, it has been distributed for free.
''Ha'ir'' is published on a Thursday evening, and is distributed throughout the metropolitan area of Tel Aviv through newspaper stands.
One of ''Ha'ir'''s supplements is ''Akhbar Ha'ir'' ({{Lang-he|עכבר העיר}}, lit. ''City Mouse''), a Tel Aviv entertainment guide.
In December 2009, distribution of Ha'ir was stopped to residents of [[Holon]] and [[Petah Tikva]] after research with [[focus group]]s found that residents are not interested in the content that is seen as more relevant to Tel Avivians.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.globes.co.il/news/article.aspx?QUID=1055,U1261997378283&did=1000525677|script-title=he:מצמצמים חלוקה: תופסק הפצת עיתון "העיר" בחולון ובפתח-תקווה|author= Lior Aberbach |date= 27 December 2009 |work= |publisher= Globes |accessdate=27 December 2009|language=he}}</ref>
