[[File:HK Wan Chai Lockhart Road 338 HK Buddhist Association.JPG|thumb|Headquarters of HKBA on [[Lockhart Road]].]]
'''Hong Kong Buddhist Association''' ({{zh|t=香港佛教聯合會|j=hoeng1 gong2 fat6 gaau3 lyun4 hap6 wui2}}) is a [[Buddhist]] organisation in Hong Kong founded in 1945.  It promotes Buddhism in Hong Kong and provides a series of charity services in Hong Kong, including education, medical, child care, youth activities, elderly care and burial.

The association also runs the [[Buddhist Fat Ho Memorial College]], founded in 1977.

