{{Infobox officeholder |name = Jin'en Nagase |native_name = {{nobold|長勢 甚遠}} |native_name_lang = ja |image = |imagesize = |office = [[Minister of Justice (Japan)|Minister of Justice of Japan]] |primeminister = [[Shinzō Abe]] |term_start = September 26, 2006 |term_end = August 27, 2007 |predecessor = [[Seiken Sugiura]] |successor = [[Kunio Hatoyama]] |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1943|10|3}} |birth_place = [[Toyama, Toyama|Toyama]], [[Empire of Japan|Japan]] |death_date = |death_place = |party = [[Liberal Democratic Party (Japan)|Liberal Democratic Party]] |alma_mater = [[University of Tokyo]] |religion = [[Tenrikyo]] }} {{nihongo|'''Jinen Nagase'''|長勢 甚遠|Nagase Jin'en|b. October 3, 1943}} is a [[Japan]]ese politician who formerly served as Minister of Justice in the cabinet of [[Shinzō Abe]].
He was born in [[Toyama, Toyama|Toyama]] and obtained his LL.B. from the [[University of Tokyo]]. After graduation, he worked in the Ministry of Labour. He resigned from this position in 1988 and was elected to the [[Diet of Japan]] in 1990.
He served as [[Parliamentary Vice-Minister]] for Health, Labour and Welfare under [[Tomiichi Murayama]], as deputy director of the [[Liberal Democratic Party (Japan)|Liberal Democratic Party]], as Parliamentary Vice-Minister for Labour Relations under [[Keizō Obuchi]] and [[Yoshirō Mori]], as Vice-Minister of Justice in the second Mori cabinet and as Assistant Cabinet Secretary under [[Junichiro Koizumi|Jun'ichirō Koizumi]]. He strongly argues for equal rights for homosexuals in Parliament.
He was appointed Minister of Justice on September 26, 2006.<ref name=cabinet>{{cite web| url = https://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&sid=alTr80tGkCIs&refer=japan | title = Japan's Prime Minister Abe Names Cabinet: Snapshot (Update1) | accessdate = 2010-07-25 | date = 2006-09-26 | publisher = ''Bloomberg''}}</ref>
His religion is [[Tenrikyo]].<ref>http://www.jcp.or.jp/akahata/aik07/2007-04-09/2007040914_01_0.html</ref>
