This is a '''list of [[mosque]]s in [[Turkey]]'''. As of March 2013, there were 82,693 mosques in Turkey. The province with the highest number of mosques (3,113) was [[Istanbul Province|Istanbul]] and the lowest number (117) was [[Tunceli Province]].<ref name="Haberturk2013">[http://www.haberturk.com/yasam/haber/825261-turkiyede-kac-cami-var How many mosques are there in Turkey?] Haberturk.com</ref> This reflected an increase of mosques by 7,324 in the 10-year period since 2003.<ref name="Haberturk2013"/> {{Expand list|date=May 2014}} {|class="wikitable sortable" |- !Name !class=unsortable|Images !City !Year !class=unsortable|Remarks |- valign=top |[[Sabancı Mosque]] |[[File:SabanciMosque meyavuz 20081226 06.JPG|120px]] |[[Adana]] |1998 | |- valign=top |[[Aslanhane Mosque]] |[[File:Arslanhane Mosque 01.jpg|120px]] |[[Ankara]] |1290 | |- valign=top |[[Kocatepe Mosque]] |[[File:Kocatepe Camii Ankara edit.JPG|120px]] |[[Ankara]] |1987 | |- valign=top |[[Maltepe Mosque]] |[[File:Maltepe mosque.jpg |120px]] |[[Ankara]] |1959 | |- valign=top |[[Zagan Pasha Mosque]] |[[File:Zağnospaşa Cami.JPG|120px]] |[[Balıkesir]] |1461 | |- valign=top |[[Emir Sultan Mosque]] |[[File:Emirsultan 1.JPG|120px]] |[[Bursa]] |1868 | |- valign=top |[[Bursa Grand Mosque]] |[[File:Bursa Ulucami.jpg|120px]] |[[Bursa]] |1420 |Largest mosque in Bursa |- valign=top |[[Green Mosque (Bursa)|Green Mosque]] |[[File:Bursa002.jpg|120px]] |[[Bursa]] |1421 |"Green Mosque" commissioned by [[Mehmet I]] |- valign=top |[[Evliya Kasim Pasha Mosque]] | |[[Edirne]] |1442 |Commissioned by [[Kasım Pasha]] |- valign=top |[[Selimiye Mosque (Edirne)|Selimiye Mosque]] |[[File:Edirne 7333 Nevit.JPG|120px]] |[[Edirne]] |1575 |Commissioned by [[Selim II]] |- valign=top |[[Üç Şerefeli Mosque]] |[[File:BurmalıCamiEdirne (3).JPG|120px]] |[[Edirne]] |1547 |Commissioned by [[Murat II]] |- valign=top |[[Arap Mosque]] | |[[Istanbul]] |1856 |Based upon a former Roman Catholic church devoted to Saint Paul and Saint Dominic. |- valig