The '''Simon Rockower Award'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ajpa.org/?page=RockowerAwards |title=Rockower Awards |accessdate=2017-12-29}}</ref> is an award given for "Excellence in Jewish Journalism". The award is sponsored by the [[American Jewish Press Association]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.jta.org/2017/06/15/news-opinion/united-states/jta-takes-4-rockower-awards-for-journalistic-excellence|title=JTA takes 4 Rockower Awards for journalistic excellence|work=Jewish Telegraphic Agency|access-date=2017-12-29|language=en-us}}</ref> Awards are given out at the Annual Simon Rockower Awards banquet in November of the respective year.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://forward.com/news/345224/the-forward-scoops-17-rockower-awards-from-jewish-press-association/|title=Forward Scoops 17 Jewish Press Awards|work=The Forward|access-date=2017-12-29}}</ref>
The award was originated in 1979 by the children of Simon Rockower.
